author: Reuters Editorial
title: Norwegian salmon export price fell to NOK 67.32 last week -SSB
text:
OSLO, April 25 (Reuters) - The export price of fresh farmed Norwegian salmon fell to 67.32 Norwegian crowns ($8.51) per kilo last week from 68.21 crowns the previous week, Statistics Norway said on Wednesday.
Volumes exported fell to 15,094 tonnes from 15,751 tonnes over the same period, it added.
Norway is the world’s largest producer of farmed salmon. The sector is the Nordic country’s second-largest export industry after oil and gas production.
Leading Norwegian producers include Marine Harvest, Salmar, Leroy Seafood, Grieg Seafood , Austevoll Seafood and Norway Royal Salmon . ($1 = 7.9144 Norwegian crowns) (Reporting by Oslo newsroom)
